The Rt. Hon. Ernest Marples, M.P., until recently a British Cabinet Min- ister, is still an active leader in the British Parliament. Many are aware of his political career as Minister of Transport when he won acclaim as the man who “made London traffic work.” However, few of us are aware that he is a vineyard owner in the Beaujolais area, a scholar in the field of wines, and a man dedicated to un- compromising excellence, whether it be politics, industry or wine.

During this sale period, and in anti- cipation of your Spring and Summer needs, we strongly recommend that you avail yourself of this unique op- portunity to acquire the superb red wines of Beaujolais and the white wines of Macon and Pouilly-Fuissé —all 1969 vintage—at levels consid- erably below what they are worth, and what equal quality is now de- manding on the wine market.
